def: A combining form indicating connection with, or relation to,the rectum; as, recto-vesical.
Of or pertaining to teratology; as, teratological changes.
The quality of being emphatic; emphasis.
Pertaining to, or characterized by, rheum. Rheumic diathesis.See Dartrous diathesis, under Dartrous.
One of the Poecilopoda. Also used adjectively.
A failure to attend; omission of attendance; nonappearance.
A seasoned preparation, as of chicken, lobster, cheese, orfish, cooked in a drum-shaped mold; also, a pastry case, usuallysmall, filled with a cooked mixture.
Not obedient; disobedient. [Obs.] Chaucer.-- In`o*be"di*ent*ly, adv. [Obs.]
A mental disorder in which melancholy and gloomy views tormentthe affected person, particularly concerning his own health.
That may be exercised, used, or exerted.
A very fast, unarmored, lightly armed vessel designed tocapture or destroy merchant vessels of an enemy. Not being intendedto fight, they may be improvised from fast passenger steamers.
